pageContext.claim: “So we have now over 1,000 people [from Antifa or BLM] -- federal -- in jail. We're prosecuting many people. ”
pageContext.analysis: As of Oct. 20, the federal government had arrested more than 300 people — 286 of which are defendants in federal cases — according to an AP tally. Some of those arrested do identify as part of left-wing activist groups, but others are part of right wing groups.
